The President has declared a major disaster in Oklahoma due to a severe winter storm that occurred from January 13 to January 16, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Beaver, Beckham, Dewey, Ellis, Harper, Major, Roger Mills, Texas, Woods, and Woodward are eligible for federal funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for funding. John Long has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and deemed necessary based on further damage assessments.